[{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURMemJYemFREAE","review_link":"https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURMemJYemFREAE!2m1!1s0x0:0xd11e2b0c4cd783f3!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgIDLzbXzaQ%7CCgwI36aAtAYQ6PeEiwE%7C?hl=en-GB","name":"wafa fafa'","reviewer_id":"107817602656961249324","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107817602656961249324?hl=en-GB","rating":4,"review_text":"Pasar Tani Gemas hari Sabtu.. tapak yg sama dengan pasar malam.. tak la besar sangat pasar taninye, tapi cukup la ade buah, sayur,daging tulang, ayam, ikan, baju2 and makanan yg dah siap..

Kopok lekor sedap! Gerai yg adE jual air teh and choc sekali. Agak mahal bg sy, rm2 4pcs. tapi sedap la.. panas2 lagi..hehe

Gerai yg ade jual popiah + karipap sardin pun sedap! Popiah rm2, 3pcs.. inti popiah tu antara daging, ayam cheese, crab stick and sayur. Mmg inti2 mahal ha.. karipap sardin pun sedap walaupun xnmpk sardinnye.. 

Nasi kerabu yg jual tepi sekali dgn nasi lemak berlauk pun sedap! 1 bungkus 2 org boleh makan. Portion besar! Nasi+tolo masin + solok lada + ayam/lauk lain + kopok Rm7 (bln June 2024) saje! Sambal ade 3 jenis, and kelapa sambal tu ade 2 jenis. Mmg nampak ikhlas betul mereka menjual.. tapi sbb sambal 3 jenis, agak basah  kene cepat2 makan risikk basi..

Tapai pulut yg jual kt simpang masuk pun sodap!  TQ pakcik jual tapai yg sodap 

Overall pasar ni ok.. worthit la pegi.. just kalau boleh manage sampah2 dengan lebih baik lebih la bagus.. good luck korg!","published_at":"a year ago","published_at_date":"2024-06-29T13:59:59","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":89,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":270,"is_local_guide":true,"review_translated_text":"Saturday Gemas Farmers Market.. the same site as the night market.. the farmers market is not very big, but there are enough fruits, vegetables, meat, chicken, fish, clothes and ready-made food..

Kopok lekor is delicious! The stalls there sell tea and chocolate. A bit expensive for me, rm2 4pcs. but it's delicious.. hotter..hehe

The stalls that sell popiah + sardine curry puffs are also delicious! Popiah rm2, 3pcs.. the popiah filling is meat, chicken cheese, crab stick and vegetables. The filling is really expensive.. the sardine curry puffs are also delicious even though you can't see the sardines.. 

The kerabu rice that is sold on the side with nasi lemak with side dishes is also delicious! 1 pack can feed 2 people. Large portions! Rice + salted tolo + pepper solok + chicken/other side dishes + kopok Rm7 (June 2024) only! There are 3 types of sambal, and there are 2 types of sambal coconut. They seem really sincere in selling.. but because there are 3 types of sambal, it's a bit wet so eat it quickly and risk going stale..

The sticky rice they sell at the entrance is also delicious! Thank you for selling the delicious tapai 

Overall, this market is ok.. worth going to.. just if they can manage the garbage better, it would be even better.. good luck to found out about this when I wanted to go somewhere on a Thursday night and realized that this place is open.
It's not hard to get there, pretty close to an MRT station,  few stops away from downtown like Bukit Bintang can get there within 30 minutes.
It's quite a happening place, and there was a lot of variety of food. The food sold is quite diverse and you don't really see repeats so it was worth the effort to walk from one end to another, not very long if you were to just walk workout stopping then it's 5 minutes.
Recommended that you start walking from one end where the shopping mall is to the other end, then make a you turn back. In this way you would have seen all the stalls then decide what to buy as you make your way back.
Some of the stuff looks pretty good, with pretty reasonable prices. I saw one which caught my attention, it was the one selling the salted egg dishes, think it's called Ultraman or something. Looked good and the food was like cooked in front of your eyes. I decided to buy and was a regret that it tasted cold, and it was quite expensive ordering a mixed bag.
The one I ordered and I liked was the mee jian kueh (also known as Kam Long bao) and the yam dessert. It was good, cheap and filling.

Can get crowded starting between 5:30 p.m. to 5:45 p.m; at that time, finding the nearest parking spot to the Pasar Malam entrances can be obviously difficult. Getting here early, at about 5 p.m, is a good thing, as most stalls have begun selling, but there are some stalls that are not available at that time. Some stalls are opened at 5:30 p.m, and some stalls are even seen opening at 6:00 p.m!

Some of stalls I've been to are of the following:

- The Nasi Lemak Ayam Goreng Tepung stall. Loved their Nasi Lemak with their fried chicken, priced at RM5.50. The sambal has anchovies in it and is delicious. Too bad that they no longer selling nasi lemak, and opted to sell nasi ayam instead.

- LeckerEis ice-cream stall. Loved the ice-cream sold here, and has a variety of flavours to choose from.

- Al-Zahra food truck. Loved the shawarma and chicken Mandi (spelled here as Mandy or Mendy). The shawarma tasted best without the hot sauce, and I often ask for extra Toum (garlic sauce) for it. They are also available outside of the Pasar Malam spot almost everyday. As of 2023, Al-Zahra now opened a stall instead, and they seldom appear.

- The Murtabak and Vadai stall. Loved the medhu vadai (priced at 60 cents a piece; the masala vadai is also similarly priced as of 2023) and the beef murtabak (RM6.00 for one murtabak, as of 2023). They use beef chunks instead of minced beef for the murtabak. The medhu vadai is best eaten when warm.

- Chicken Chop stall. The chicken chop tasted delicious, but I would not recommend it, as I once saw the stall owner SMOKING in front of the food! Not only that, the last time I bought the chicken chop this year, it doesn't taste as good as four years ago.

- Kenari Soya Bean stall, available on Tuesdays only. Loved their soya bean drink. Sadly, this stall is no longer available as of 2023.

- 'Pasar Tani canopy' drinks stall. Used to regularly buy drinks from them. Loved their watermelon drink. Sadly, this stall is no longer available as of 2023.

- RZ drinks stall near the police station (now located behind Fix It hardware store). Loved the Chocolate Vanilla drink (my personal favourite). Their new Strawberry Mango drink is also delicious; However, they only sell it once, and have stopped selling it now, much to my disappointment.

- A family-owned fruits stall, selling one 'longgok' of fruits at RM5. Normally bought oranges and apples here. They also have Cavendish bananas, also priced at RM5 for one 'longgok'. I no longer buy from this stall now, so I don't know about the price anymore.

- Laksa Johor stall, located beside a takoyaki stall (now located behind Guardian pharmacy). They have laksa Johor and a variety of noodle dishes. The stall owners are perhaps the nicest I've ever met.

- LYNZ Nasi Lemak stall. Liked their Nasi Lemak Ayam Goreng Berempah set.

- Pasta stall. All pasta dishes sold at RM13 each (as of 2023). Loved the Spaghetti Bolognese and Spaghetti Carbonara set.

- EMA Satay stall, normally located beside LYNZ's Nasi Kukus stall, also near the police station (now located opposite RZ drinks stall). Back then, they used to regularly sell satay on both Tuesdays and Saturdays, but now they seldom appear. I used to regularly buy their chicken satay, as I find their satay is somewhat better than the other stalls available. Sadly, their satay's quality has dwindled now.

- Nasi Ayam Penyet stall, located near the tyre workshop and Empire Putra college. Here, they sell the ayam penyet set, priced at RM9 (as of 14th November 2023, it's RM10), and a RM1 add-on for the fried tofu or brinjal. Other than ayam penyet, they also have fried catfish, deep-fried prawns and also deep-fried squid rings. Personally, I loved the ayam penyet set, as it is, by far, the best I've ever had in Bandar Seri Putra.
